explanation: This solution uses a frequency count array to efficiently compare the two arrays. It iterates through the target array to initialize the count array, then iterates through the arr array to decrement the corresponding count. If any count becomes negative, it immediately returns false. If it finishes iterating through the arr array without returning false, it returns true. This approach has a high efficiency due to its constant space complexity and linear time complexity.

